        <fields>
            <name>Welcome_Text</name>
            <fieldText>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong style=&quot;color: black; font-size: 18px;&quot;&gt;Application to the Rosalind Franklin Laboratory - Laboratory Support Placement&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: black; font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;The Rosalind Franklin Laboratory (RFL) is at the forefront of diagnostic testing not only for COVID and variants of concern but also any other future health threats. This has created an exceptional opportunity for anyone wishing to embark on a career within a laboratory environment. The RFL is the UK Health Security Agency’s flagship laboratory and has access to the latest equipment and smartest minds to offer a truly unique opportunity and supportive working environment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: black; font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Our mission is to become a world-renowned diagnostic and testing laboratory.&amp;nbsp;Our world class laboratory team will use scientific innovation to accurately test at scale any known threat and we work through our values, Insightful, Impactful &amp;amp; Inclusive to achieve our mission.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: black; font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;You will have a scientific and inquisitive mindset, be willing to learn and ready to engage proactively within the laboratory environment. As a member of the RFL team, you will be expected to apply your knowledge, act professionally and adopt a proactive approach to all tasks. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: black; font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;In return, we will offer you a structured placement designed to build on your knowledge, provide exposure to all areas of RFL activity needed to effectively run a high-throughput laboratory and develop the all- important employability skills you will need for your future career. A dedicated Placement Co-ordinator will provide mentorship and pastoral support to ensure you are able to successfully complete the placement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: black; font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;The number of placements is limited. To register your interest, please begin your application now.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em style=&quot;color: black; font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;Please note, although this portal is operated on behalf of the UKHSA (Health Security Agency), employment opportunities are through third party suppliers such specialist workforce providers.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</fieldText>
            <fieldType>DisplayText</fieldType>
